62.9	Blended_learning	Blended learning	Blended learning in educational research refers to a mixing of different learning environments. It combines traditional face-to-face classroom methods with more modern computer-mediated activities. According to its proponents, the strategy creates a more integrated approach for both instructors and learners. Formerly, technology-based materials played a supporting role to face-to-face instruction. Through a blended learning approach, technology will be more important.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Blended-learning-methodolog.jpg/220px-Blended-learning-methodolog.jpg
